<h1>
<seg id="1">The cancellation of law about the social activities - this is not the solution of problem.</seg>
</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">Last week Constitutional Court annulled law about the social activities.</seg>
<seg id="3">Decision caused the lively discussion in the society.</seg>
<seg id="4">Undoubtedly, it will interestingly look at this problems from a wider point of view.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5">the Liberal-oriented economic systems in the European Union, just as in globalizovannom peace, are based on the principle of the plural, uncontrolled economic competition.</seg>
<seg id="6">In the essence this means that the separate economic subdivisions, national economic systems, are found in a constant conflict with each other.</seg>
<seg id="7">This is connected with the principle of free trade and free, with anything unconfined motion of the private capital together with the unbridled financial speculation.</seg>
<seg id="8">Price stress appears as a result of the substantial difference in the cost of labor force (wages).</seg>
<seg id="9">By this concept it is necessary to understand the state, when producer by means of the delivery of budget item tries to withstand in the economic competition by the fact that he " brings down” the cost of competitor for the purpose to take away to himself the large part of the market and to, thus, increase his own income.</seg>
<seg id="10">On a mass scale this indicates for the majority of owners either the transfer of production for the boundary or cheap purchases abroad, or disappearance. As a result rises unemployment in those in the countries, where the cost of labor force, in comparison with others, high.</seg>
<seg id="11">Since the private capital bears no social responsibility, including for unemployment the produced by it, the inevitable expenditures of state for social needs grow.</seg>
<seg id="12">As a whole, the situation strengthens the unwillingness of gentlemen of owners to pay taxes and to thus compensate the public economic and social damage, applied by them in pursuit of profit.</seg>
<seg id="13">Situation is so well known that it is not necessary to cite concrete statistical data.</seg>
<seg id="14">The unceremonious methods of the private capital are created at the level of the economies of the individual states of the situation, when the governments of the countries are forced to enter into the competition with each other in order to artificially reduce the social level of its population for the purpose of attraction into the country of the foreign capital.</seg>
<seg id="15">In other words, governments return their own population to the arbitrariness to the private capital, in spite of the social decline.</seg>
<seg id="16">This finds, first of all, its reflection in changes in the current legislation.</seg>
<seg id="17">Purpose it is to economically force its people to obey the dictates of the private capital, first of all in the region of wages.</seg>
<seg id="18">This acts as the system of economic coercion in the case of the long-term unemployment and it at the same time serves as the tool of urezaniya of the rights of workers in the sphere of working legislation.</seg>
<seg id="19">As a result rises the level of poverty, and at the same time also the difference between the poor and rich.</seg>
<seg id="20">IN the FRG already for several years there is a public distribution of the products poor, which one cannot feed itself by its own labor.</seg>
<seg id="21">A quantity of these people already approaches million.</seg>
<seg id="22">Within the framework of an increase in the competitive ability of German economy constantly occur the cases, when the job-placed people obtain such wage, which state to them must pay the remainder so that they would obtain the subsistence minimum.</seg>
<seg id="23">A similar scandal became known to community, also, in the case of the additional workers of Bundestag.</seg>
<seg id="24">Economic measures practically in all southern states the European Union, undoubtedly, lead to the same state, in which the people, which are found under the pressure of a catastrophic drop in social status, are forced either to emigrate, as this was in the 19th century or exist to the beggarly wage in the rear of society in the hope, that sometimes into the country will arrive particular investment capital.</seg>
<seg id="25">However, it does ask itself, from where it will undertake?</seg>
<seg id="26">If capital arrives from other countries the European Union, then poverty move of one country into another, or it will not arrive generally, since Chinese, Hindu, Brazilian, Turk, marokkanets, Egyptian, African still work for a fraction of European wages.</seg>
